Vihiga United FC captain Patrick Okulo now wants his teammates to improve their game in the remaining matches to avoid relegation. Speaking at Senende High School training ground, Okulo said: “We have no choice but to work extra hard in the remaining matches if we are to avoid relegation,” he said. The team is currently placed  17th on the log with  11 points from 16 matches. “For the remaining phase of the league, we need to focus and improve our results if we are to stay in the top tier,” he said. Okulo said though the club is facing numerous challenges financially at the moment, they still have a chance to survive.